[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide − French"]
[Black "Fort Knox 3.Nc3 dxe4 4.Nxe4 Bd7"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6
{ The French Defense got its name after Paris beat London in a correspondence match in 1834, successfully adopting this opening with Black. The French is different than other openings after 1.e4 − the structures we are going to see are not often seen in other openings @@StartBracket@@especially the Winawer@@EndBracket@@, which makes it difficult to handle with the white pieces. }
2. d4 d5 3. Nc3
{ The fashion changes, but  3.Nc3  remains the main move. Not only is the Knight developed to the most active square, but in a way we are also anticipating  3...c5  . }
3... dxe4
{ Black has released the tension in the center. In general, this should be good news for White. }
4. Nxe4 Bd7
{ Quite a popular continuation in rapid/blitz time controls. Black has a simple plan: to put the Bishop on c6, the Knight on d7, and only then develop the other Knight to f6. }
5. Bd3 { The first couple of moves are pretty obvious for both sides. } 5...
Bc6 6. Nf3 Nd7 7. O-O Ngf6 8. Nc3
{ Normally we don't want to put the Knight in front of the c2-Pawn as we would like to advance it to c3 or c4 at some point. However, keeping an eye on the d5-square is more important.   8.Nxf6+  Qxf6!  should be okay for Black. @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/pppn1ppp/2b1pn2/8/3PN3/3B1N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 7 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Ng3  is  by far the most popular move in the position, however, the Knight is not so well placed on g3. The solution I would like to recommend to you looks rather stupid but has a very good tactical explanation. }
8... Be7 { The most natural and likely continuation. } 9. Re1 O-O
{ So far everything is exactly like after 8.Ng3. What is the difference? } 10.
Ne5
{ Let's come back to @@StartFEN@@r2qkb1r/pppn1ppp/2b1pn2/8/3PN3/3B1N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQ1RK1 w kq - 7 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Ng3  Be7  9.Re1  O-O  10.Ne5  . Now Black has  10...Nxe5  11.dxe5  Qd5!  This is why we need to control the d5-square. }
10... Nxe5 { After this, White's advantage will be overwhelming. } 11. dxe5 Nd5
12. Qg4
{ Black won't even have time for  12...Nxc3  due to  13.Bh6!  After @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/ppp1bppp/2b1p3/3nP3/6Q1/2NB4/PPP2PPP/R1B1R1K1 b - - 2 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Re8  13.Ne4  White's attack will be too strong to parry. }
