{ This is possible, although a bit inconsistent from Black to not push the Pawn to h4. }
9. g4 hxg4 10. hxg4 Bb7
{ 11.f3  e5  would be just fine for Black so we have to do more than that. }
11. g5 Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Bxe4 13. g6
{ When the opponent moves the Rook to g1, many of us smile gently but then the Rook proves really useful on this square! }
13... Bxg6 14. Rxg6 { Of course! } 14... fxg6 15. Qg4
{ This is much stronger than  15.Ne6?!  Qc8! } 15... Ne5 16. Qg2
{ The Queen is beautifully placed here! White has a great advantage − we want to castle and then push f2-f4. Black has weak light squares, the Bishop trapped on f8, and the King in the center. }
