{ Isn't Black just winning the Bishop? After  23.Bxe4?  Qc3+  that is certainly the case. }
23. Bd4 exd3 24. gxh5 f6 { Black didn't have a choice. } 25. cxd3
{ White has only a Pawn for the exchange but it is more important to be on the attacking side here. We are threatening h5-h6 and Qd1-h5. Black has many weak light squares and the Bishop can only go backwards. }
