{ It feels a bit random but I was trying to make normal moves with Black. } 17.
Bb6 { Useful intermezzo. } 17... Rd6 18. Bxd5 Rxd5 19. Rd1
{ White is slightly better. We want to move the King to e2 and then the Knight will come to either c4 or e4. Why is White better here? There are two main reasons:   We have a Pawn majority on the Queenside, which is generally nice @@StartBracket@@many Pawn endgames should be winning for White!@@EndBracket@@.  Black has a dark-squared Bishop and a key Pawn on the dark square @@StartBracket@@e5@@EndBracket@@. }
