{ The best defense. Black should equalize here although seeing the whole line in advance doesn't seem very likely. }
19. Nxe4 Rxd1+ 20. Rxd1 Bxe3+ 21. fxe3 Nxg4 22. Rg1 { Black now has a choice. }
22... h5
{ Both  22...Nxe3  23.Rxg7  and @@StartFEN@@2k4r/1p3ppp/p7/8/P3N1n1/2P1P3/1P5P/2K3R1 b - - 1 22@@EndFEN@@  22...Nxh2  23.Rxg7  would offer White some winning chances. }
23. h3 Nxe3 24. Rxg7 Rd8
{ Black is threatening mate in one, which gives a precious tempo. } 25. Kb1 f5
{ Black should play actively. } 26. Nc5 Rd5
{ Hoping for  27.Nxb7  f4!  and  with the Knight trapped on b7, White has to be careful not to lose this one. }
27. Ne6
{ With such active pieces, we don't need to be worried about the result although to be fair, we have to admit that Black is also quite active. The draw seems like the most likely outcome. }
