6... b5
{ The most aggressive reaction. It is like an invitation to dance − it would be a pity to decline. }
7. a4 { Not the only move, but it is the most challenging one. } 7... b4
{ This is by far the most popular continuation and also a critical one. } 8.
Nd5 Nxe4
{ I think this is the sharpest possible line in the whole 6.Rg1 system. } 9.
Bc4
{ This is the best try, and it was already played in the game between Maxime Vachier-Lagrave and Ding Liren in Opera Euro Rapid, chess24 2021. }
9... e6 10. Qe2 { White has so many active pieces! } 10... Nc5
{ Basically the only move. } 11. c3
{ Following in the Frenchman's footsteps, we want to undermine the Knight's position, which is the only piece that Black has developed so far! }
11... bxc3 12. b4 Ncd7 { The most natural reply but tactically risky. } 13. Bg5
Nf6 14. O-O-O
{ White and Black combined managed to break all the most important rules of chess: development, King's safety, etc. :@@EndBracket@@ }
14... Be7 15. Nxe7 Qxe7 16. Rge1
{ We are threatening Nd4-f5 and since  16...e5?  17.Qf3!  is winning for White, Black should not fight it but rather embrace it. }
16... O-O 17. Nf5 Qb7 { At least Black will find some counterplay. } 18. Bxf6
Qxb4 { These are all only moves for Black. } 19. Nh6+ Kh8 20. Be7 Qa3+ 21. Kb1
Ra7 { Still the only moves.  21...Qb4+  22.Ka1!  and White wins. } 22. Bxf8
Rb7+ 23. Bb5 axb5 24. Nxf7+ Rxf7
{ 24...Kg8??  would be too much as  25.Nxd6  wins. } 25. Bxd6 Qb3+ 26. Kc1 Qxa4
{ 26...bxa4  27.Qc2  . } 27. Qc2 Qa1+ 28. Qb1 Qxb1+ 29. Kxb1 Nc6 30. Bc5
{ White maintains winning chances although Black should be able to survive with accurate defense. If we look at the whole line from the beginning, this looks like mission impossible for Black. }
