{ Capturing the c3-Pawn is our plan at the minimum. } 15... O-O
{ The best defense. } 16. Nf5 { This looks like a cheap trick. } 16... Qf6 17.
Nh6+ { Surprising resource! } 17... gxh6
{ Now White's attack is really strong. } 18. g5 Qe5 19. Be3 h5
{ 19...Kh8  would lose to  20.f4!  Qg7  21.gxh6  Qf6  22.O-O-O  Nc6  23.Qg4  . }
20. Bd3 c2 { Black might as well skip it. } 21. Rc1 Nd7 22. Qxh5 Qc3+
{ 22...Qg7  23.Rh3  f5  24.gxf6  Nxf6  25.Qh4  and White is winning. } 23. Bd2
Qg7 24. Bxc2
{ Despite being a piece down, White should be winning. We have a slow and brutal plan: Bc2-b1, Rc1-c4-h4 @@StartBracket@@or -g4 and then g5-g6!@@EndBracket@@. Black should also watch out for an immediate g5-g6!?. }
