{ If we can't win the b4-Pawn we can trade it. We will still have the edge on the Queenside. }
16... bxc3 17. b4 Nd7 18. b5 axb5 19. Bxb5
{ White has nice compensation for the Pawn. Our passed Pawn is strong and Black still needs to connect the Rooks @@StartBracket@@to be fair, so do we@@EndBracket@@ After  19...Ba8  20.Bc6  is strong, while after @@StartFEN@@1r2kb1r/1b1n1ppp/3p4/PB1Pp3/8/2p1N3/5PPP/R1B1K1R1 b Qk - 0 19@@EndFEN@@  19...Bc8  , we should retreat with  20.Be2!  ,  keeping the a6-square under control. }
