{ This is widely considered to be the most challenging continuation. White wants to castle long and developing the Bishop to g5 first is the best way to do it. We should note that after both  6.Be3  Ng4  and @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pp2pppp/2np1n2/8/3NP3/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6.f3  e5  , Black benefits from developing the  Knight to c6 instead of putting the Pawn on a6. }
