18... Rg8 19. g3 Qc7
{ Black is ready to retreat the Knight to b6 so it's best to swap it. } 20.
Bxc4 Qxc4 21. a3
{ This slow improving move indicates that a long game is ahead of us, but it's mostly a problem for Black who has most of the pieces on the back rank. White has a big advantage. We actually have a typical case of Knights being superior to Bishops in the Rauzer structure.  We can slowly improve with moves like Qe1-f2 and Rd1-d3. We will probably play f4-f5 and then start thinking about improving the position of our Knight on c3. One thing that White always has to watch out for is a possible counterstrike in the center, most likely ...d6-d5. As long as the position is closed, the Bishop will be very passive, but once it opens up we have to be ready. }
