{ This is more accurate than  15.Bc4  Qc7  and Black is ready to meet  16.h4  with  16...Rad8! }
15... Nf4
{ In a way, this is a capitulation. Black is asking for an inferior endgame. }
16. g3
{ The more aggressive  16.Qe1  is also possible but I really see no need for complications here. }
16... Qxd2+ 17. Rxd2 Nh5 { 17...Nd5  would be met in the same way. } 18. g4 Nf4
19. g5
{ Fixing the Pawn structure on the Kingside. Once again, White has a long-term advantage in the endgame. We can develop the Bishop to d3 and then put our Queenside Pawns on b3 and a4 and move the Rook to d1. At some point, we can maneuver the dark-squared Bishop to the long diagonal. }
