16. Re1
{ Taking the Pawn would require a lot of accuracy. Instead, White simply consolidates the position. }
16... Be6 17. h4 Rfd8 { The most natural move. } 18. h5
{ It is less about attacking the King and more about gaining the h4-square for the Rook. }
18... Rd7 19. Bd3 Qxe3+
{ Black could no longer tolerate White's Queen due to the Qe3-h6 threat. } 20.
Rxe3 Kg7 21. Rh4
{ White has a long-term advantage. The Rooks are very active on the 3rd and 4th ranks. Let's make a lift with b2-b3 and then try to attack Black's weaknesses. Imagine our h4-Rook on a6! In some cases, we might even swap the Bishops with Bd3-c4, which would give our Rooks even more space to operate. }
