[Black "Sicilian 2.Nf3 d6 − 4.Nxd4 e5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 e5
{ I think this move exists only as a reminder that Black should start with ...a7-a6 first. }
5. Bb5+ { Now Black is facing a difficult choice. } 5... Bd7
{ The light-squared Bishop is that one piece Black does not want to trade. The d5-square was already weak and it will become even weaker. }
6. Bxd7+ Qxd7 7. Ne2
{ Any retreat would be okay here but this one is probably the best, the Knight has good prospects on e2. }
7... Qc6 8. Nbc3 Nd7 9. a4 { All the light squares are ours. } 9... Ngf6 10. f3
{ White is much better. We want to bring the Knight to g3, provoking ...g7-g6.  10...Qb6  is not a problem since we have  11.Qd3  followed by Be3,  while  11...Nc5  can be met by  12.Qb5+  , with a better position. }
