7. O-O e5 8. a3 Ne7 { Black decides to not fight our plan. } 9. b4 cxb4 10.
axb4 O-O 11. Na3
{ With the black Knight on e7 controlling d5, aiming for c2-c4 and b4-b5 made far less sense. }
11... Be6 12. Nc4 Qc7
{ Notice how unpleasant  12...Bxc4  13.dxc4  would have been for Black. White has such a good game on the a-file whereas all of Black's pieces are passive. }
13. Ne3
{ White is better. The Knight is nicely placed on e3. We want to put the Bishop on b2 and push c2-c4. After that, we should be flexible − b4-b5, c4-c5, and d3-d4 are possible under the right circumstances. }
