8... O-O 9. Nc3 Ne8 { Plan B. } 10. Bf4
{ Once again, with ....b7-b6 played already, we can develop the Bishop to a more active square. }
10... Nc7 11. Qd2 Ne6 12. e5 { 12.Bh6  was also pleasant. } 12... Nd4 13. Nxd4
cxd4 14. Ne4
{ Quite a typical position in this line. It looks innocent and Black is indeed solid. However, Black has no active plan and the idea that might ever have a nice battery on the long diagonal will be dealt with in one move. }
14... Qd5 15. Ng3 c5 16. b3 { So we wouldn't have to worry about ...c5-c4. }
16... Bb7 17. f3
{ We have already seen this resource in part one in some of the Ruy Lopez positions. One simple Pawn move is enough to neutralize Black's most dangerous weapon. White is slightly better and we have a simple plan: double on the e-file and advance the h-Pawn. }
