{ Castling suggests that Black may be intending to bring the Knight to c7 although different plans are still possible. }
8. O-O Qc7 { Just another little move from Black. } 9. Be3 b6 10. Qd2 e5
{ If you play  11.Bh6  here, I won't blame you, although Black is a bit better prepared for it, just as in the previous line.  11...Nh5  12.Bxg7  Nxg7  . }
11. Rae1
{ It's a bit of an unpleasant situation for Black. Bringing the Knight to e6 is normally the plan but how to do it now? }
11... Nh5 12. Ne2
{ We deliberately refrain from moving the Bishop to h6, let Black worry about what to do next. }
12... Ba6 13. b3
{ Black would be very happy to play ...c5-c4 but our job is not to make Black happy. }
13... Rad8 { Once again, hoping for ...c5-c4. } 14. Qc1
{ White is better. We will continue with the typical Nf3-h2, and then probably g2-g4, kicking the Knight back, and only then f2-f4. The other possibility is to just go g2-g4 and Ne2-g3. }
