{ White's Pawn on b4 is a bit more dangerous than Black's Pawn on c4. We are also threatening g2-g4.   Computers keep the balance with the surprising  24...Bh6!  intending to answer  25.g4  with  25...Ne3!  Good luck to Black with finding that one,  but if that happens, we'll just move the King's Rook to a1. }
