{ 6...Ba6?!  7.Nbd2  Qa5  8.Rb1  transposes. } 7. Nbd2 Qxc5 8. O-O Nf6
{ Black's point is that after  9.Re1  , there is  9...Ng4  . } 9. Nb3
{ It is not easy to find the right place for the Queen.  9...Qb6  10.e5  Ng4  11.Qe2  is clearly better for White, while @@StartFEN@@r1b1k2r/p2pppbp/2p2np1/2q5/4P3/1N3N2/PPP2PPP/R1BQ1RK1 b kq - 3 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Qh5?  10.e5!  Ng4  11.Bf4  is even bigger. }
