11. fxe3 Be7 12. Nc3 O-O 13. e4
{ We don't really want to win the d5-Pawn @@StartBracket@@unless there is some specific point@@EndBracket@@ as it would open the whole position and this is exactly what Black's passive Bishops are hoping for. Instead, we should try a Kingside attack − Qd1-e1, Nc3-e2-f4, h4-h5, etc... }
