{ White takes on c6 right away in order to damage Black's Pawn structure. }
4... bxc6 5. d3 d5
{ The 2nd most popular move in the position but to me, it just looks like a concession. Black usually tries to avoid this Pawn structure. }
6. b3 Nf6 7. Qe2
{ I like it more than the short castle plan. I am not saying we will castle long, but we might. }
7... Be7 8. e5 Nd7 9. Nbd2
{ I'd like to give some high-class comments but White's moves are too natural. }
9... O-O 10. Bb2
{ I like the idea of castling long. We can then advance our Kingside Pawns freely and we should always stop Black's a-Pawn with a2-a4. }
