{ White takes on c6 right away in order to damage Black's Pawn structure. }
4... bxc6 5. d3 Ne7
{ This is by far the main continuation, although I am not sure if it's the best one. }
6. Nbd2
{ The latest trend, already played by Grischuk and Giri. The point is exactly the same as after  6.Qe2  , which is one of the well-known moves. We are delaying castling in order to  keep the h2-h4 advance possible in case of ...Ne7-g6. Compared to 6.Qe2, our choice works well against 6...d6 too. }
