{ I think it's good to have this option, it's just more aggressive than  12.Ne3  . The Queen has attacked  the d5-Pawn  and Black can't defend it with  12...Ne7  because of  13.h6!  , while @@StartFEN@@r1b1k1nr/p1q3pp/2pb1p2/2ppp2P/4P3/3PN3/PPPNQPP1/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 5 12@@EndFEN@@  12...d4?  13.Nec4  would be just horrible. }
12... c4
{ Thematic breakthrough − Black is sacrificing a Pawn in order to fix the Pawn structure and damage ours. }
13. dxc4 d4 14. Nb3 Qf7
{ 14...c5  is possible but after  15.h6!  I think that White is better. } 15.
c5 Bc7 16. Bd2
{ We will bring the Knight to d3. We probably want to castle short but first, we have to retreat the other Knight to h2 so the h5-Pawn is protected. Our long-term plan will be to open up the position with c2-c3. White's chances are preferable, although the position remains complicated. But hey, wasn't that our goal from the very beginning? }
