10... Ng8 { It's the only way to develop the dark-squared Bishop. } 11. Ng4 Bd6
12. Ne3 Ne7 13. g4
{ We didn't have to do it now but also there was no reason to delay it. This plan is quite common in this position and similar structures. For instance, we can also find it in Anti-Berlin: @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  e5  2.Nf3  Nc6  3.Bb5  Nf6  4.d3  Bc5  5.Bxc6  dxc6  6.Nbd2  O-O  7.Qe2  Re8  8.Nc4  Nd7  and now the topical plan for White is to advance the g- and h-Pawns. }
