11. Nd5 d6 12. c3
{ This is just an improved version of the main line. We will be focusing on the Queenside, so b2-b4 is the plan. The other idea is to go Nf3-e1 and then g2-g3 followed by Ne1-g2-e3. If we manage to add h2-h4, then we will achieve a perfect setup with Black's dark-squared Bishop neutralized. }
