{ Currently, this aggressive move is one of the main challenges for Black. In some ways, it is similar to the  7.Qd2  line,  but there f2-f3 is played automatically, whereas here, at least in some lines, we can skip it and save time. }
7... Bb4 { The second most popular continuation but it's not good for Black! }
8. Nxc6 Bxc3+
{ This intermezzo is basically the only way to stay in the game for Black. } 9.
bxc3 bxc6 10. Bc5 { It's already awkward for Black. } 10... d5 11. Qd4 Nf6
{ 11...e5  12.Qa4  . } 12. exd5 cxd5 13. f4
{ White has prevented ...e6-e5 and is now ready to develop the Bishop to d3. I think Black has to try to go ...Bc8-d7 and ...Ra8-c8. Let Black win this c3-Pawn and swap the Queens, we will get fantastic compensation on the b-file. }
