{ Somehow we transposed to one of the Najdorf lines. } 12... Nd7 13. f4
{ 13.h4  would be met with  13...Ne5  , which explains our choice. } 13... Bb7
14. h4 Nc5 15. Bg2 { White's plan is simple: advance the Kingside Pawns. }
15... Qb6
{ It is what the engines are recommending for Black @@StartBracket@@at least initially@@EndBracket@@, which makes sense but White is faster. }
16. g5 { 16.b4?!  a5! } 16... a5 17. f5 b4 18. f6
{ As I said, White is faster. } 18... bxc3 19. Qxc3 Bd8 20. fxg7 Re8
{ Black is a piece up so we have to play energetically. } 21. g6 fxg6 22. h5 g5
23. Rhf1 { White is threatening Qf3. } 23... g4 24. Rf8+
{ The next moves are forced. } 24... Rxf8 25. gxf8=R+ Kxf8 26. Bxc5 Qxc5 27.
Qh8+ { We will win the Bishop on b7. White should be winning here. } *

