[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6
{ This line has become very popular, and most of the Sveshnikov players use it at least occasionally in order to avoid the Rossolimo. }
6. a3
{ Putting the Pawn on a3 so early has been one of the biggest developments in the Sicilian Defense in recent years. It can be tried against many different versions of Taimanov/Kan/Paulsen. }
6... Be7
{ The most critical response. Black keeps the Pawn on a7 and the Queen on d8, so in the case of long-castle plans, there will be more options available. }
7. Nxc6
{ I consider it a very good practical try, played by Anand and Caruana, among others. }
7... dxc6 { A passive response. } 8. Qxd8+ Bxd8 9. e5 Nd7 10. f4 f6
{ Black wants to get rid of our e5-Pawn, which is understandable but it's damaging Black's Pawn structure too. }
11. exf6 Nxf6 { 11...gxf6  12.Ne4  is better for White. } 12. Bd3 Bd7 13. Bd2
{ We will castle long and place our Rooks on e1 and f1. White is slightly better as Black has a passive light-squared Bishop and a weak Pawn on e6. }
