Rxc1 Nf4 15. Qc3
{ We are ready to sacrifice the g2-Pawn in order to prevent ...Qd8-a5+. } 15...
Nxg2+ 16. Kf1 f5 { The only move. } 17. Nd6
{ 17.Nf6+?!  Rxf6  18.exf6  Nf4  and Black will  win the f6-Pawn. } 17... Qg5
{ Black has to be extremely precise.  17...Nf4  18.h4  would be already much better for White. }
18. Ra1 { 18.Rd1?!  f4!  and Black is  threatening ...Ng2-e3+. } 18... Nh4 19.
Rg1 Qh6 20. Re1
{ The position is unclear but Black's task is harder since the pieces lack coordination while we have a great Knight on d6. }
