8. Bd3 Nf6 9. O-O Bb7 { Black wants to place the Pawn on c5. } 10. Be3 c5
{ 10...d6  11.c5!  and White is much better. } 11. f4 d6 12. e5
{ Tactics work in our favor because of Black's poor development. } 12... dxe5
13. fxe5 Qxe5 { Taking the Pawn is losing by force. } 14. Qa4+ Nd7 15. Bf4 Qd4+
16. Kh1
{ The Bishop cannot be touched but anyway Black has no way of stopping Ra1-d1 and then removing the light-squared Bishop from the d-file will decide. }
