8. Nxc6 dxc6 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. e5 Ne4
{ The active way is not always a better way! } 11. a3 Bxc3+ 12. bxc3 Kc7
{ The greedy  12...Nxc3  is met by  13.a4  and after  13...Ne4  14.Be3  f6  15.Bd3  Ng5  , White is spoilt for choice as almost any move is more or less winning.  16.O-O  ,  16.f4  , or  16.exf6  and White has a huge initiative. }
13. Be3
{ Black is too badly developed to take the c3-Pawn.  13...Nxc3?!  14.h4!  followed by Rh1-h3-f3 and it's difficult for Black to defend. }
13... b6 14. h4
{ We want to bring the Rook to g3, forcing ...g7-g6, and then attack the Pawn on f7. The other idea is just to push the h-Pawn. The Knight can be kicked out from e4 with Bf1-d3. }
