{ Believe me, you want to do it. I never score well against it and many players with Black just hate it. Besides, the alternatives are not that great.  5.Bd3  Bc5  I like for Black, @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/1p1p1ppp/p3p3/8/3NP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nc3  b5  I like for Black too. @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/1p1p1ppp/p3p3/8/3NP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.a3  is interesting, but this would mean that Kan is as serious as Taimanov and it's not.  After @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/1p1p1ppp/p3p3/8/3NP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.c4  , Black has one correct way of playing that is pretty close to equality, but it also leads to a position that is very impractical, as you shall see. The point of our last move is to improve White's control in the center and  anticipate ...b7-b5 or ...d7-d5. }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 Bb4
{ The main continuation, although grandmasters Artur Neiksans and Igor Kovalenko don't recommend it in their LTR on the Kan, which pretty much confirms that the best line, objectively, might not be the best practical choice. }
7. Qd3 { The Queen defends both the Knight and the e4-Pawn. } 7... Qc7
{ The most popular move in the position, although Black seems to be in trouble. }
8. a3 Be7
{ Black's claim is that no tempo has been lost for ...Bf8-b4-e7 because the Queen is misplaced on d3 − it is not. }
9. f4 d6
{ 9...O-O  10.Be2  Nc6  11.Be3  d6  12.O-O  e5  13.Nf3  exf4  14.Bxf4  would transpose. }
10. Be2 b6
{ The Hedgehog is an interesting structure but if White is too active, it might end up badly. }
11. b4 Bb7 12. Bb2 Nc6 13. Nc2
{ White has no reason to swap pieces with such a space advantage. } 13... O-O
14. O-O
{ White is clearly better. Our plan is to attack on the Kingside and we can just push the Pawn to g5. But there is one condition: each time we must be absolutely sure that Black won't be able to counterattack with ...d6-d5 or, less often, ...b6-b5.   Therefore, for instance after  14...Rfd8  , we should stop and check  15.g4  d5  . It actually works for Black so, instead, we should go @@StartFEN@@r2r2k1/1bq1bppp/ppnppn2/8/1PP1PP2/P1NQ4/1BN1B1PP/R4RK1 w - - 7 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Rad1  . }
