{ Black's Bishop is misplaced on a5, it should have remained on the a3-f8 diagonal. }
9. Qg4 { Who is going to defend the King now? } 9... O-O
{ 9...Kf8  10.Qg3  ,  stopping ...d6. White can follow up with natural developing moves and the usual attacking plan: h2-h4-h5. }
10. Bd3 d6 11. Nf3
{ It would be naive to think that White's intention was to defend the e5-Pawn.  11...dxe5??  will be met with  12.Bxh7+  . }
11... f5 12. exf6 Rxf6 13. Ng5 Rh6
{ 13...h6  14.Ne4  Rf7  15.Qg6  and Black will suffer material consequences. }
14. O-O Nc6 15. Rae1 Ne5 { Otherwise, we were ready to take on e6. } 16. Rxe5
dxe5 17. Nf3 Rf6 18. Bg5
{ Black is lost, we are threatening Qg4-e4, provoking ...g7-g6. After  18...Qf8  19.Bxf6  Qxf6  , White has  20.Qa4  . }
