10... Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qe5+ 12. Be3 Qxd6 13. Nb5
{ Once again, we are sacrificing the Pawn but the positional trumps that we are getting in return are simply too big. }
13... Qxd1+ 14. Rxd1 O-O 15. Nd6
{ We can develop the light-squared Bishop to e2 and castle, or just push the h-Pawn. In each case, White has a big advantage. }
