{ There are far too many games played in this line − it is just too weak! } 8.
Na4 { The only good reaction. } 8... Qa5+ 9. c3
{ No need to worry about the Knight, it is not going to get lost. } 9... c4
{ Forcing our hand... } 10. b4 Nxb4
{ This piece sacrifice is just incorrect as Black won't be even close to obtaining reasonable compensation. However, some accuracy will be required from us. }
11. cxb4 Bxb4+ 12. Kf2 b5 { This is rather automatic. } 13. Nb2
{ There were other moves such as  13.a3  , but this seemed the strongest. Now White is threatening 14.a4 so Black should move the dark-squared Bishop. }
13... Bc3
{ Black is hoping to create some chaos on the board but is basically operating with only two pieces. }
14. Qc2 b4 { An important moment as we can now gain a decisive advantage. } 15.
Rc1
