13... Ba3 { A better choice than  13...Bc3  . } 14. Qc2
{ However, it is not clear how Black can claim any compensation at all. For now, we can just ignore Black's Queenside Pawns as they pose no danger to us. }
14... Nb6 15. g4
{ This is one useful nuance to know: we should keep the Bishop on f1. The point is that sooner or later our Queen might be chased away from c2, for instance, ...Bc8-d7, ...b5-b4, ...c4-c3, and ...Bd7-a4.  In such a case, the Queen should be able to operate on the 2nd rank and for that, we need our Bishop to stay away from e2. White's plan is clear: advance the Kingside Pawns. We can continue with h2-h4-h5 and f4-f5. The King will be safe on g3. }
