11... Bxc5 12. Nb3 { As usual, we are happy to swap the dark-squared Bishops. }
12... Bxe3 13. Qxe3 Qb6 { 13...Qc7  14.Bd3  would be just better for White. }
14. Qxb6 Nxb6 15. g3
{ The point of our last move was not to prepare the fianchetto but to improve our Pawn center. The f4-Pawn is the key and it has to be defended. As usual with the light-squared Bishops on the board, White enjoys a long-term advantage. }
