12... Bxc5 13. Bd3 Ra7
{ The best defense. Black is waiting for a perfect moment for ...f7-f6 and then the Rook will be defending the 7th rank. }
14. Qe1
{ This is less popular but in my opinion stronger than  14.g4  f6  15.exf6  gxf6!  where things are not so clear. White is now  threatening Bd3xh7+, forcing Black's reaction. }
14... f6
{ 14...Be7  would be answered by  15.h4  with attack. The text move is part of Black's plan but the moment wasn't  perfect − our Pawn is still on g2! }
15. exf6 gxf6
{ Both  15...Qxf6  and  15...Rxf6  would be answered with  16.Ne4!  dxe4  17.Qxe4  winning the piece back with a great advantage. }
16. f5 { Destroying Black's Pawn center. } 16... exf5 17. Nh4
{ White is better. We will win the Pawn back and with a superior Pawn structure and active pieces, it will be much easier for White to handle this position. }
