7... Be7 8. Qd2 a6
{ Black is preparing the b-Pawn advance while delaying castling. } 9. Bd3
{ 9.Be2  is much more popular but I am not sure why.  The Bishop on d3 works clearly better against Black's typical setups simply because the Bishop is better placed on d3. }
9... O-O
{ Objectively the best but I don't think you will find too many opponents who will willingly enter this wild line. }
10. dxc5 Nxc5
{ 10...Bxc5  is no difference as Black falls under the same tactical shot with  11.Bxh7+  Kxh7  12.Bxc5  Nxc5  13.Qf2  and Black is unable to defend  the Knight on c5 and parry the Ng5 idea at the same time. }
11. Bxh7+
{ Once again, we are using this typical motif.  11.Bxc5  Bxc5  12.Bxh7  Kxh7  would transpose. The next moves are forced. }
11... Kxh7 12. Bxc5 Bxc5 13. Ng5+ Kg8 14. Qd3 Re8 { Basically, the only move. }
15. Qh7+ Kf8
{ 16.Qh8+?  would not be a good idea.  16...Ke7  17.Qxg7  Qd7!  and the black King will hide on d8. }
16. Qh5
{ This way we are dragging the Black Queen to c7 where, along with the other pieces, it will build some sort of a wall preventing their own King from escaping. But first, let's see why it has to be 16...Qc7. }
16... Qd7
{ This move looks terrible but, given that Black is now threatening both  17.--  Ke7  and  17.--  f6  we should not ignore it. Plus the refutation is really cute. }
17. Na4
{ The dark-squared Bishop doesn't seem to be the crucial defender here but in fact, it is one! }
17... b6
{ 17...Ba7  would only make it easier with White responding in the very same way. }
18. Nxc5 bxc5 19. Nh7+
{ The point of the whole operation. Black can't go  19...Kg8  as after  20.Nf6+  gxf6  21.exf6  , mate is unavoidable. This also explains why we had to get rid of that Bishop,  so Black wouldn't have had ...Bc5-f8 at the end of that line. }
19... Ke7 20. Qg5+ f6 21. Nxf6
{ 21.exf6+?  Kd6!  would suddenly become unclear. } 21... Qb7 22. Ne4+ Kf8 23.
Nd6 Qd7 24. O-O
{ The Knight is stronger than the Rook. Let's continue the attack instead. We can push f-pawn and we can also bring the Rook to f3. White should easily win this one. }
