{ 9.Be2  is much more popular but I am not sure why.  The Bishop on d3 works clearly better against Black's typical setups simply because the Bishop is better placed on d3. }
9... O-O
{ Objectively the best but I don't think you will find too many opponents who will willingly enter this wild line. }
10. dxc5 Nxc5
{ 10...Bxc5  is no difference as Black falls under the same tactical shot with  11.Bxh7+  Kxh7  12.Bxc5  Nxc5  13.Qf2  and Black is unable to defend  the Knight on c5 and parry the Ng5 idea at the same time. }
11. Bxh7+
{ Once again, we are using this typical motif.  11.Bxc5  Bxc5  12.Bxh7  Kxh7  would transpose. The next moves are forced. }
11... Kxh7 12. Bxc5 Bxc5 13. Ng5+ Kg8 14. Qd3 Re8 { Basically, the only move. }
15. Qh7+ Kf8
{ 16.Qh8+?  would not be a good idea.  16...Ke7  17.Qxg7  Qd7!  and the black King will hide on d8. }
16. Qh5
{ This way we are dragging the Black Queen to c7 where, along with the other pieces, it will build some sort of a wall preventing their own King from escaping. But first, let's see why it has to be 16...Qc7. }
16... Qc7 17. O-O-O
{ A tricky moment for Black as the next move is far from obvious. } 17... Bd4
{ Definitely a difficult move to make if you don't know it's the one. ...Bd4xc3 is a threat we should not ignore. }
18. Ne2
{ I had a hard time deciding what the best try would be here and eventually decided to settle for this one.  18.Rd3  would be another possibility. }
18... Bc5 { There is no fun for Black having to be nice all the time. } 19.
Rhe1
{ This wasn't the only try, but it's very dangerous and less obvious than  19.Qh8+  or  19.c4  . Naturally, we are assuming our opponent willingly entered this sharp line, otherwise, any of these moves should do the job. }
19... Ke7
{ Basically, the only move I can think of, but at the same time, it is not an easy decision. Black has to evacuate the King. }
20. Nc3
{ 20.Qxf7+  Kd8  wasn't worth it. With the text move, White is intending to strike in the center. }
20... Bd4
{ The Bishop is covering the d-file again, but this time it won't stop us. }
21. Qxf7+ Kd8 22. Nxd5 { Clearly, the Rooks in the center will be useful now. }
22... exd5 23. Qxd5+ Ke7
{ White should gain a clear advantage after this move. } 24. f5
{ 25.f6+ is a deadly threat. } 24... Qd7 { The only move. } 25. f6+ Kd8 26.
Qxd7+ Kxd7 { 26...Bxd7  27.f7  . } 27. e6+ Kc7 28. f7
{ It's surprising that with such Pawns White isn't just winning here. } 28...
Rf8 29. e7 Bd7 30. exf8=Q Rxf8 31. h4 { Anticipating Black's next move. } 31...
Bf6 32. Rf1 Ne5
{ Black will win our key Pawn but don't worry, we will get another one. } 33.
Rde1 Bxg5+ 34. hxg5 Rxf7 35. Rxf7 Nxf7 36. Re7 Nxg5 37. Rxg7
{ I honestly don't know if White is winning here but surely has good chances for it. }
