Nb6 { This plan is not really dangerous with the Queen on c7. } 15. Bd3
{ Let's stop for a moment.  15...b4  leads nowhere.  16.Bxb6  Qxb6  17.Na4  and Black has no clear way of challenging White's setup on the Queenside. After  17...Qc7  18.g4  , it is just much better for White.   15...Nc4  is no better.  16.Bxc4  bxc4  @@StartBracket@@  16...dxc4  17.Nc5  would be even worse@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/2q1bppp/p1n1p3/3pP2P/2p2P2/1NN1B3/PPPQ2P1/1K1R3R w - - 0 17@@EndFEN@@  17.Nd4  and after  17...Rb8  , White is just in time with  18.Ka1!  and once again, Black is left with no counterplay. }
