14... Bb7 15. Qh3 g6 { Now we should anticipate ...d5-d4. } 16. Rhf1
{ You already saw why White should not worry about ...Bb4xc3. After  16...Rc8  , we can finally move  the Knight to e2 with an enormous advantage. }
