12... b5 13. Kb1
{ If you feel nervous over the board @@StartBracket@@our main line does have a small margin of error@@EndBracket@@, then here's a safe and strong backup. }
13... Bb7 14. a3 Be7 15. Ne2
{ This works better with the 13.Kb1 Bb7 inclusion. White has an easy game. We can move the Knight from e2 to d4 or try Rh1-f1-f3-h3. For Black, the task is much harder as ...b5-b4 can always be answered with a3-a4. }
