{ The decisive intermezzo. After the immediate  26.Qxf5?  , Black has a lucky escape:  26...Qa5!  ,  activating the Queen just in time. }
26... Qxb6+
{ A sad necessity.  26...Qa8  27.Qxf5  would be hopeless. There is no way to  defend the f7-Pawn, given that the dark-squared Bishop would be hanging too. After Rb7xf7 followed by e5-e6, Black is crushed. }
27. Rxb6 Be3+ 28. Kf1
{ 28.Kh1  should be winning too, but in this case, it is useful to bring the King to the center. It will help White to deal  with the c4-Pawn. }
28... Bxb6 29. a4 { Black is losing the Bishop too. } 29... Bxa4 30. Qxb6 c3
31. Ke1
{ Black's Queenside Pawns will quickly fall. As long as White doesn't blunder any of the kingside Pawns, there will never be any fortress. }
