13... Bb7 14. h5 { 14.Rh3  is also possible. } 14... h6
{ Stopping the h-pawn makes sense, but now there is a new plan: g2-g4-g5. } 15.
Qe3 { A good improving move. } 15... Rc8
{ 15...Bxd4  would be met by  16.Rxd4  with full control. } 16. Kb1
{ Not the only move, but it is a standard reaction to Black occupying the c-file. }
16... Bxd4 17. Rxd4 f6
{ Once again, it looks like the only reasonable direction. } 18. exf6 Qxf6 19.
Be2
{ White is better. Our long-term plan is to advance the g-pawn @@StartBracket@@g2-g4-g5 and sometimes f4-f5@@EndBracket@@, but first, we should make sure to control the center as ...e6-e5 might be a potential threat. For that reason, moves like Be2-f3 and Rh1-e1 look sensible. }
