12. b4 d4 { Otherwise, White would be completely winning. } 13. Nxd4 Nxd4 14.
Bxd4 Nxc5 15. Be2
{ But not  15.Bxc5?  Bxc5  16.bxc5  Qd4+!  17.Kh1  Qxc3  and Black is doing great. }
15... Ne4 16. Nxe4 Bxe4 17. c3
{ There is no need to dwell on details, White is just a Pawn up and Be2-f3 seems like a natural follow-up. }
