7. dxc5
{ It is a good moment to come back a bit. Why didn't we take on c5 right away? After @@StartFEN@@rnbqk1nr/pp3ppp/4p3/b1ppP3/3P4/P1N5/1PP2PPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6.dxc5  Bxc3+  7.bxc3  Qc7!  , Black is forcing us to move the Knight  to f3, and the Queen won't get activated at all. }
7... Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Nd7
{ This is just a blunder. We didn't take the g7-Pawn right away, but that doesn't mean we forgot about it! }
9. Qxg7 Rg8 10. Qxh7 Nxe5 11. Qh5 Nf5 12. Nf3
{ White's advantage might be just winning already. After all, we are two Pawns up, so I think it's safe to say we will keep at least one of them. }
