{ We can't allow Black to close the position on the Queenside as well. } 12...
Qa5 13. Rb1 { Preparing Rb1-b5. } 13... Nge7
{ Black correctly assesses that development is more important, but it is not enough now. }
14. Rb5 { The next few moves are rather obvious. } 14... Qc7 15. Bd3 O-O 16.
Ne2
{ White has a clear advantage. We can castle and then try to finish development. The Bishop will be well placed on e3. }
