4. e5 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7 { 6...Qc7  7.Qg4  Ne7  would transpose. } 7.
Qg4 Kf8 8. a4
{ Especially with the King on f8, the idea of bringing the Bishop to a3 makes perfect sense. }
8... Nbc6
{ This developing move is quite often weak as it does not help in any way dealing with the light-squared Bishop problem. }
9. Nf3 Qa5 10. Bd2 c4
{ You already know that this means one-way traffic but on the other hand, it was hard to recommend anything else for Black. }
11. h4
{ White is much better. We will push the Pawn as far as possible @@StartBracket@@I assume it will reach h5 and there it will be stopped@@EndBracket@@, and then put the Bishop on e2, castle, and prepare the g-Pawn advance. }
