22... Ng7 23. Be5 Qd8
{ White would be better after almost any move here, but with some accuracy, we can maximize the profit. }
24. Be4 Be6 25. Bxg6 { A classical advantage conversion. } 25... hxg6 26. Bxg7
Kxg7 27. Rxe6
{ The minor pieces are gone, but Black is still in great trouble with the numerous weaknesses: b7, d5, and most importantly, g6. }
27... Qh4 28. Qe1
