10. Bd2 Rg8
{ That's one possibility. Starting with @@StartFEN@@rnb1k2r/ppq1nppp/4p3/3pP3/2pP2Q1/P1P5/2P1BPPP/R1B1K1NR b KQkq - 1 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Rg8  would be inaccurate, as White could consider  10.a4!?  Qa5  11.Qh3  followed by Qh3-e3, Be2-g4, Ng1-e2, and eventually the dark-squared Bishop would achieve the a3-square.   The other option would be to defend that Pawn with the King: @@StartFEN@@rnb1k1r1/pp2nppp/4p3/q2pP3/P1pP2Q1/2P5/2P1BPPP/R1B1K1NR w KQq - 1 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Kd2  Nbc6  12.Nf3  Bd7  13.Ba3  O-O-O  14.Rhb1  and Black is not in time with  14...f6  , as White has  15.Rb5  Qa6  16.Qh5  with a big advantage. }
11. Qh3 { This plan works well with the Bishop on d2 as well. } 11... h6 12. a4
{ Making sure that Black won't block this square with the Queen. } 12... Nbc6
13. Bh5
{ This is the essence of White's plan − now Black will have a hard time castling without compromising the dark squares on the Kingside. }
13... Bd7 14. Ne2 Rf8 { Black is fighting hard to avoid ...g7-g6. } 15. Qf3
{ OK but can we really take the f7-Pawn? Let's find out! } 15... O-O-O 16. Bxf7
{ 16...Be8??  17.Bxe6+  is easy. White is now  threatening Qf3-h5 while  @@StartFEN@@2kr1r2/pp1bnBp1/2n1p2p/q2pP3/P1pP4/2P2Q2/2PBNPPP/R3K2R b KQ - 0 16@@EndFEN@@  16...Ng6  can be answered with  17.Qg3  Ngxe5  18.Bh5  with a great advantage. }
16... g6
{ The only challenging move. We can't take  17.Bxh6?  as after  17...Rh8  , either the other Rook is  coming to f8 or White runs into  18.Bg7  Rh7  19.Qf6  Nxd4!  and Black is better.  20.Bxg6  is met with  20...Ng8!  Remember this line as it will serve as our reference point. }
17. h4
{ This is the critical moment. White has a slow but effective plan of bringing the Rook to f4. Black can't move the Bishop with the King on c8, so two moves have to be considered here: }
17... Kc7 { Option no. 1. } 18. Bxh6 { Now this works. } 18... Rh8 19. Bg7 Rh7
20. Qf6 Nxd4 { Let's find out why it doesn't work now. } 21. Bxg6 Ng8
{ What has changed? } 22. Qxd8+
{ In our reference line, Black would be able to recapture with the Queen but now it is not possible. }
22... Kxd8 23. Bxh7 Nxe2 24. Kxe2 Qxc3 25. h5
{ As long as there is no perpetual @@StartBracket@@and there isn't!@@EndBracket@@ White is completely winning. }
