a4 Nc6 16. Bc2
{ Once again, Black has a problem with the g7-Pawn.  16...O-O  gives White a too strong attack after  17.Nf3  f6  18.Bxf5  exf5  19.Qg3  . }
16... Rg8
{ Black managed to defend against the most direct threats and it's time to slow down. }
17. Qd1
{ Whether Black decides to retreat the Queen or try to keep it active, does not change our plan. Apart from Rc1-b1, we want to develop the Knight to e2, push the black Knight back with g2-g4 and then finish development with f2-f3 and Ke1-f2.  Long-term we want to achieve g4-g5. White clearly has the advantage here, simply it's going to take some time before we can actually advance. }
