{ There is a lot of compensation for the Bishop. } 27... Nh4
{ 27...Ne7?!  28.Rxe6  Rh7  29.Nd4  and White is better. } 28. Rxe6 Bf3 29.
Rxf6+ { An important moment for Black. } 29... Ke8 { A losing mistake. } 30.
Nd4 Bxg4 31. f5
{ White is threatening both Nd4-e6, followed by Ne6-g7+ and Rf6-d6#, and Nd4-c6 and Ra7-e7#. The best Black can do is to give up a piece with  31...Nxf5  , but the resulting endgame is just winning for White. }
