Nd5+ Rf7 35. Nf6
{ A useful trick.  35...Rf5!  is now the only move, after which White wins back the piece and maintains serious pressure in the endgame.  36.Rxf7+  Kxf7  37.Nxg4  Rxf4  38.Ne5+  Ke7  39.Rb6  Rf1+  40.Kb2  Nf3  41.Nxf3  Rxf3  42.Rxb5  . The opening is over, yeah... The endgame is of course theoretically drawn, but tell that to the many grandmasters who have lost it. }
