4. Bd3 { Once again... } 4... c5
{ The main move, both here and after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/3PP3/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nd2  Be7  4.Bd3  .  The Knight is better placed on c3 as it directly attacks Black's d5-Pawn. }
