{ The fashion changes, but  3.Nc3  remains the main move. Not only is the Knight developed to the most active square, but in a way we are also anticipating  3...c5  . }
3... c5
{ I have no idea why this move is so popular, it's just a huge blunder. } 4.
exd5 exd5 5. Bb5+ Nc6 6. dxc5 Be6 7. Be3
{ Black just can't win the Pawn back. } 7... Ne7 8. Nf3 Nf5 9. Bd4
{ Actually, it's a matter of preference as  9.Bg5  or  9.Qe2  are equally strong. }
9... Be7 10. b4 O-O 11. Bxc6 bxc6 12. O-O
{ After  12...a5  13.a3  , White is just a Pawn up, there is zero compensation for Black. }
