11... Nb6 12. Be4 { Aimed against ...Bc8-d7. } 12... Nd5 13. Qd3
{ The h7-Pawn is hanging. } 13... h6 { Now White's attack is even stronger. }
14. Ne5 Bd7 15. Qg3
{ 15...Kh8??  16.Qh3!  followed by 17.Bxh6 is  already winning, which means that Black has basically lost the h6-Pawn. }
