15... exd4 16. e5 Bb4 17. Rf1
{ Now there is even more pressure on the f7-Pawn. } 17... c5
{ The only challenging move. The 'solid'  17...Rae8  18.Rxd4  would be much better for White. }
18. a3 Ba5
{ Important moment − White's next moves are not obvious at all and we have to make them! }
19. e6 fxe6
{ 19...f5  20.Nxd4!  cxd4  21.Rxd4  is winning as Black can't stop Rd4-d7. }
20. Nxd4 { But what is this? } 20... cxd4 21. Bxe6+ Kh8 22. Bc8
{ Straight from a puzzle book! By combining different tactical motifs, White wins the piece back and since Black's Bishop is not really a piece right now, we are easily winning here. }
