4... a6 { Black wants to play ...c6-c5 but first, Bf1-b5+ is anticipated. } 5.
h5
{ The Pawn is always nice on h5. By the way, the simple  5.c4  would also be pleasant, which would be an improved version of @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.e4  c6  2.d4  d5  3.e5  Bf5  4.c4  . }
5... c5 6. dxc5 Nc6 7. Bd3 Qd7 8. Be3 { Let's provoke ...d5-d4. } 8... d4 9.
Bf4 e6 10. Nd2
{ The Pawn is not really strong on d4 while White has gained nice squares for the Knight. }
10... Bxc5 11. Ngf3 O-O-O { 11...Nge7  12.h6!  would be nice. } 12. a3 Nge7 13.
Bg3
{ Anticipating ...Ne7-d5. If Black goes  13...Nd5  anyway, then White is better after the simple  14.Qe2  followed by castling Queenside. }
