16... b6 17. d6 { 17.b4!?  would be another try. } 17... Ng6
{ 17...Nf5  18.d7+  would be even better. Black's Knight does not defend the Rook  on h8 which, as you shall see, is quite important. }
18. d7+ Nxd7
{ 18...Ke7  or  18...Kd8  would be unthinkable. Just  19.b4  and White is winning. }
19. Rxd7 Rc8
{ Thanks to this trick, Black can survive. If anyone wants to abort here then  20.Qd1  is the way:  20...Rxc1  21.Rd8+  with perpetual check. }
20. Rc7 Rxc7 21. Qxc7 O-O 22. Qc2
{ The position is around equal but Black still has to be careful. The King is not that comfortable due to the potential back-rank problems. }
