11. Qd1
{ 11.Qxb5  cxb5  is not even worth considering with Black gaining the c-file for free. }
11... c5 { The point of Black's previous move. } 12. a4 Qb6 13. dxc5 Bxc5 14.
Nxc5 { There was no reason to refrain from this. } 14... Qxc5 15. Re1 Nc6 16.
c3
{ White is slightly better. Black's problem is the same as always: the h5-Pawn. After  16...O-O  17.Bf4  , Black will have to watch out  for Nf3-h2, hoping to meet ...g7-g6 with Bf4-g5 and g2-g4  @@StartBracket@@this is why the Knight should come to h2@@EndBracket@@. Black can try some waiting moves but it's never easy as White just seems to have more of them. }
