13... Bxc5 { The main move. } 14. Re1
{ We are not neglecting the possibility of exchanging the Bishop, simply we don't need to do it right away. }
14... Nc6 15. Nxc5 bxc5 16. c3
{ I believe that White is just slightly better here. Black's main problem is that due to the weak h5-Pawn, castling is problematic. For instance, after  16...O-O??  17.Nh2  g6  18.g4!  White already has a winning attack.   Black can of course try to delay castling for as long as possible but, for example, after  16...Rb8  17.b3  , there just don't seem to be any sensible moves, while White, besides the Kingside attack, also has a positional plan to  achieve c3-c4. }
