{ White is ready to bring the Knight from b3 to d3. } 13... c5 14. dxc5
{ A new move. White wants to bring the Knight to d4. } 14... Bxc5 15. Nfd4
{ We don't mind taking the Bishop in general, but starting with  15.Nxc5  Nxc5  16.Nd4  would allow Black to release at least part of the tension with  15...Qd3  . }
15... Ne7 { Reasonable but passive. } 16. Nxc5 Nxc5 17. Bxe7 Kxe7 18. Re1
{ White wants to bring the Rook to e3. } 18... Qd3 { The best response. } 19.
Qc1
{ As you have probably noticed, we generally don't want to trade the Queens as Black's King is weak in most lines. }
19... Qg6 20. Qe3
{ With the Queen on g6, this makes more sense than Re1-e3. The point is that now Black has to watch out for the Queenside as well! Even the Queen can't be in two places at the same time! Our plan is to bring the Rook to d1 and then relocate the Knight to g5 while the Rook will take its place on d4. White enjoys a big advantage. }
