21. Nxd4 Nxd4 22. cxd4 Rfc8 23. Nd3
{ The Knight is well placed on d3 − it creates some attacking possibilities but more importantly, it defends White's weak Pawns on b2 and d2. }
23... Nb8
{ Black's Knight on d7 was totally misplaced. Also, the pseudo-active  23...Rc2?  24.Qe3  would only lead to big problems for Black. }
