{ The most practical try. The Rook will protect the Knight, allowing us to activate the Queen. }
24... Nc6 { This natural follow-up is a losing mistake. } 25. Qg5
{ The Knight is heading to f4. } 25... Nxd4 26. Nf4 Nc2 27. Re2
{ Actually, White is in no hurry here. We want to protect the Rook with Rdd2 and then there will be too many threats for Black to handle them all: Nf4xg6, Nf4xh5, and g2-g4. }
27... d4 { Black is hoping to use the long diagonal. } 28. Kh2
{ Not only moving away from possible check but also making space for the Rook. }
28... Qb7 29. g4 hxg4 30. Qxg4
{ White has a winning attack as Black has run out of resources to disturb us. }
