{ This is important. White is preventing any possible counterplay on the Queenside. To make it clearer:  12.Be2?!  b6!  13.cxb6  Nfxd4!  followed  by 14...Qxb6 would already be fine for Black,  while @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pp2bppp/2n1p3/2PpPn2/Q2B4/2P2N1P/PP3PP1/R3KB1R b KQ - 2 12@@EndFEN@@  12.Bb5?  Nfxd4!  would leave White with no good response as  13.cxd4??  would drop the piece after  13...Qa5+  .  After the text move, White has a big advantage already. We want  to go Bf1-b5, while  after @@StartFEN@@r2q1rk1/pp2bppp/2n1p3/2PpPn2/Q2B4/2P2N1P/PP3PP1/R3KB1R b KQ - 2 12@@EndFEN@@  12...a6  , the simple  13.Bd3  is strong. }
