{ I'm only covering this move because there are people on earth who played it. It contradicts the ideas of the Caro-Kann @@StartBracket@@developing the light-squared Bishop@@EndBracket@@ and it basically transposes to the Advance Variation of the French Defense with a tempo down for Black. Playing almost any opening a tempo down with Black is a terrible experience. }
