13. Nh4 Nd7 { Black is regrouping. } 14. O-O-O Ne5 15. Bh6
{ Clearly, we don't mind swapping the dark-squared Bishops. } 15... Bxh6 16.
Qxh6 Nf7 17. Qe3
{ White has an outstanding position. We can try to open it up with f2-f3 or just push the Pawn to f4. Black has no real counterplay. }
